      "id": "CVE-2026-8507",
      "publishedDate": "2026-05-17T18:43:05.863Z",
      "lastModifiedDate": "2026-05-17T18:43:05.863Z",
      "description": "Crypt::OpenSSL::PKCS12 versions through 1.94 for Perl have out of bound (OOB) write flaws.\n\nWhen parsing a PKCS12 file, with a >= 1 GiB OCTET STRING (or BIT STRING) attribute on a SAFEBAG, via info() or info_as_hash(), a heap-OOB-WRITE would be triggered which could have Remote Code Execution (RCE) potential.",
